      <div xml:id="NA128-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu kuṟai nērnta tōḻi talaivi kuṟai nayappak kūṟiyatu.
            2. tōḻikkut talaivi aṟattoṭu niṉṟatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what the confindante who agreed to [his] request said so that SHE would grant the request.
            2. It is also how SHE stood up with virtue (~ revealed the truth) to [her] confidante.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA128">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            pakaleri cuṭariṉ mēṉi cāyavum</l>
<l>            pāmpūr matiyi ṉutaloḷi karappavu</l>
<l>            meṉakkunī yuraiyā yāyiṉai niṉakkiyā</l>
<l>            ṉuyirpakut taṉṉa māṇpiṉē ṉākali</l>
<l>            ṉatukaṇ ṭiciṉāl yāṉē yeṉṟunaṉi </l>
<l>            yaḻuta lāṉṟici ṉāyiḻai yolikura</l>
<l>            lēṉal kāvali ṉiṭaiyuṟ ṟoruvaṉ</l>
<l>            kaṇṇiyaṉ kaḻalaṉ ṟāraṉ ṟaṇṇeṉac</l>
<l>            ciṟupuṟaṅ kavaiyiṉa ṉāka vataṟkoṇ</l>
<l>            ṭaḵtē niṉainta neñcamō </l>
<l>            ṭiḵtā kiṉriyā ṉuṟṟa nōyē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">“Although [your] body is emaciated</l>
<l rend="indent3">as the glow of a flame at midday,</l>
<l rend="indent">although the brightness of [your] forehead is hidden</l>
<l rend="indent3">like the moon crept over by the snake<note place="foot">This seems to be an allusion to the Rāhu myth. For parallels see KT 395.4, NA 377.7f., Kal. 140.14.</note>,</l>
<l>you do not talk to me anymore.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Since</l>
<l rend="indent2">I am glorious as if I had distributed life to you,</l>
<l>I see that indeed.”</l>
<l>Leave off saying [thus and] crying abundantly,</l>
<l rend="indent4">o you of choice jewels.</l>
<l rend="indent">That someone,</l>
<l rend="indent3">slipping between the guards of the millet with sprouting ears,</l>
<l rend="indent3">one with a chaplet, one with an anklet, one with a garland</l>
<l rend="indent3">embraced [my] waist<note place="foot">T.V.G. explains <term xml:lang="ta">ciṟupuṟam</term> to mean "waist."</note> coolly – taking in that,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with a heart that thought “that [is it]” –</l>
<l>this has become the pain I had.<note place="foot">A poem without clear-cut references. The speech-situation, however, seems to be that of HER conveying the truth to the confidante, who had noticed physical changes in her and complained about her lack of trust.</note></l>
        </lg>
         </div>
